Caliper is an independent, clean-room reimplementation of a curated-tool + agent
architecture. It does not incorporate source code from the projects below; they are
acknowledged as conceptual prior art that informed the design:

  - Biomni (snap-stanford), Apache License 2.0 — general-purpose biomedical agent.
  - cmbagent (CMBAgents), Apache License 2.0 — astronomy planning & control agent.
  - Mephisto (ZechangSun), MIT License — SED-modeling LLM agent.

The domain tools referenced by Caliper's packs (e.g. STAR, DESeq2, MACS2, Scanpy,
Astropy, emcee) are separate works distributed under their own licenses. Caliper
invokes them; it does not redistribute them. Review each tool's license before any
